                <h1>Misdemeanors: Do They Ever Go Away?</h1>
                <p>Yes, misdemeanors can eventually go away, but the process often depends on the jurisdiction and specific circumstances. In some cases, after a set period without further offenses, a misdemeanor may be eligible for expungement or record sealing, allowing individuals to move forward without the burden of past mistakes on their record.</p>
